She glared at Quet. Wanting so desperately to let him have it for dragging 
Scourge into this. Even Scourge didn't have rights to staying here. No one 
should stay here. Somehow, she had to make sure of that. It was a mistake she was 
not bound to make again. 

"I think Rodimus Prime has the last word on this one." Pausing a moment. "As 
to why... that is my own personal reasons," she glared at Quet. All she knew 
is she felt.. for once. It's not a plan well thought out decision, but a drive &
 desire to protect those she cared for... especially one in particular.


--part1_192.1b4204e7.2c0ed555_boundary
